humind.data

humind.data provides dummy data based on the 2024 MSNA indicator bank and kobo template, with some additions (e.g. expenditures). It also provides some script examples for composing indicators, analysing with impactR.analysis, and very basic visualizations.

This repository may be subject to many changes in the coming year, and mainly showcases examples to try out humind and subsequent analyses.

Installation

You can install the last version of humind.data from GitHub with:

# install.packages("devtools")
devtools::install_github("impact-initiatives-hppu/humind.data")
